<DOC><DOCNO> WSJ871020-0082 </DOCNO><HL> Mentor Corp. Clears Buy-Back</HL><DD> 10/20/87</DD><SO> WALL STREET JOURNAL (J)</SO><IN> MNTRBUYBACKS, REDEMPTIONS, SWAP OFFERS (BBK) </IN><DATELINE> SANTA MONICA, Calif.  </DATELINE><TEXT>    Mentor Corp. said its boardauthorized the buy-back of as many as two million of itscommon shares from time to time on the open market.   The medical and health products concern, which has 11.6 million common shares outstanding, said the buy-back will depend on several factors, including the price of the stock, the company's business and financial position, and general economic and market conditions.    In national over-the-counter trading yesterday, Mentor closed at $7, down $1.75. </TEXT></DOC>